---
description: Code quality, security, and accessibility standards
alwaysApply: true
---

Use semantic HTML by default.
Add ARIA attributes only when necessary.
Ensure keyboard navigation for interactive elements.
Manage focus for modals, menus, forms.
Do not store secrets in frontend code.
Avoid dangerouslySetInnerHTML without sanitization.
Sanitize all user content.

Use `.env` files for configuration (`.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.production`).
Do not store secrets in `.env` files; use secure vault for production.
Type environment variables through configuration object.
Validate all environment variables on application startup.
Use Vite env variables with `VITE_` prefix for Vite projects.
Use Create React App env variables with `REACT_APP_` prefix for CRA projects.

Implement ESLint + Prettier for code consistency.
Provide exceptions to recommended rules inline only with justification.
Setup pre-commit hooks (husky + lint-staged): formatting and linting.
Use conventional commits and semantic-release workflows.
Automate formatting and linting.
